  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Upgrade the R4 stub implementation of `DocumentViewerWidget` (the Workspace widget
    introduced in R4 task 042 / W-4 as the receiving widget for Assistant → Workspace
    `widget_load` dispatch per FR-02 / OC-R4-07) so it consumes the extracted
    `RichFilePreview` renderer from `@spaarke/ui-components` (extraction landed in task
    013) INSTEAD OF the current monospace-text-preview shim. This is the second half of
    D2-08 — task 013 extracted the renderer; this task wires the Workspace destination
    to it.

    Scope discipline (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 — reuse mandate):
    - MUST consume the extracted `RichFilePreview` primitive — do NOT inline preview
      logic, do NOT rebuild iframe / metadata pane / 3-dot menu chrome.
    - MUST preserve the existing Workspace registration (`DOCUMENT_VIEWER_WIDGET_TYPE =
      'document-viewer'`, displayName, category, icon, allowMultiple, defaultOrder) so
      every existing Workspace dispatch (R4 `useChatFileAttachment` → ConversationPane
      → `workspace.widget_load`) continues to resolve to this widget unchanged.
    - The widget's typed `widgetData` payload (`DocumentViewerWidgetData`) MUST remain
      back-compat — at minimum the existing R4 fields (`filename`, `contentType`,
      `sizeBytes?`, `textContent`) are still accepted; any new optional fields needed to
      drive the renderer (e.g. `documentId`, `documentType?`, `createdBy?`, `createdAt?`,
      `previewUrl?` or `fetchPreviewUrl?`) MUST be ADDITIVE and OPTIONAL so existing R4
      dispatch sites keep compiling without modification.

    Backward-compatibility surface: existing R4 dispatch sites pass in-memory text-only
    payloads (no SharePoint Embedded `driveId`/`itemId`). When the payload carries no
    preview URL source, the widget MUST gracefully degrade by passing a
    `fetchPreviewUrl` that resolves to `null` (which the extracted renderer already
    handles via its error/retry path per task 013 acceptance criteria). When future
    dispatch sites (e.g. R5 task 020 chat-pane orchestration, R5 task 021 per-file
    affordance) supply a preview URL source, the renderer renders the full rich preview
    via iframe.

    This task touches frontend TypeScript only — zero BFF code changes; zero new
    Dataverse data; zero PCF deployment. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend engineer with Fluent UI v9 + React 19 expertise and deep familiarity
    with `@spaarke/ai-widgets` Workspace widget composition (registry + dispatch via
    `workspace.widget_load` per ADR-030), and the `@spaarke/ui-components`
    `RichFilePreview` renderer (extracted in task 013). Comfortable reading the R4 stub
    end-to-end before re-wiring it, preserving the widget's `WorkspaceWidgetProps&lt;T&gt;`
    contract, and keeping back-compat for existing dispatch payloads.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx`
    is upgraded from the R4 monospace-text-preview shim to a thin Workspace wrapper that
    mounts `&lt;RichFilePreview /&gt;` (imported from `@spaarke/ui-components`) inside
    its existing `WorkspaceWidgetProps&lt;DocumentViewerWidgetData&gt;` envelope. The
    widget registration in `register-document-viewer-widget.ts` is UNCHANGED. The
    `DocumentViewerWidgetData` payload shape is back-compat: existing required fields
    (`filename`, `contentType`, `sizeBytes?`, `textContent`) remain accepted; new
    optional fields needed to power the renderer are ADDITIVE. Dispatch sites currently
    in R4 (text-only payload) continue to mount the widget and the renderer degrades
    gracefully to its error/retry state when no preview URL source is supplied.
    Dispatch sites that DO supply a preview URL source render the full rich preview
    (iframe + metadata pane + Prev/Next + 3-dot `DocumentRowMenu`). Existing
    `DocumentViewerWidget.test.tsx` is updated to reflect the new composition; new
    tests cover the renderer-consumption path + back-compat path. Dark-mode parity
    verified. `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5.
  </goal>

