  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (CRITICAL)">MUST consume the extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer from `@spaarke/ui-components` — do NOT rebuild iframe / metadata pane / 3-dot menu chrome inside the widget. R5 reuse mandate explicitly prohibits "parallel file-preview component to `RichFilePreviewDialog` (extract renderer, don't rebuild)"; this task is the consumption half of that mandate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (backward compatibility)">Existing Workspace dispatch sites (R4 `useChatFileAttachment` → ConversationPane → `workspace.widget_load`) MUST continue to resolve to `DocumentViewerWidget` with NO change to dispatch payload. The widget registration (`DOCUMENT_VIEWER_WIDGET_TYPE = 'document-viewer'`, displayName, category, icon, allowMultiple=true, defaultOrder=150) MUST remain UNCHANGED.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (typed payload back-compat)">`DocumentViewerWidgetData` shape MUST remain back-compat. Existing R4 fields (`filename`, `contentType`, `sizeBytes?`, `textContent`) MUST still be accepted. Any new fields needed by the renderer (e.g. `documentId`, `documentType?`, `createdBy?`, `createdAt?`, optionally `previewUrl?` or `fetchPreviewUrl?`) MUST be OPTIONAL + ADDITIVE — existing R4 dispatch sites compile without modification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (graceful degrade)">When the payload carries no preview URL source (R4-style text-only payload), the widget MUST mount the renderer with a `fetchPreviewUrl` that resolves to `null`. The renderer's existing loading/error/retry behavior handles that case (per task 013 acceptance criteria). The widget MUST NOT throw, MUST NOT crash, and MUST NOT regress R4 dispatch behavior to a broken state.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 + dark-mode parity. The upgraded widget MUST use Fluent v9 semantic tokens — NO hard-coded color literals. Dark-mode rendering MUST match light-mode visual hierarchy. The renderer already enforces this for its own subtree; the widget wrapper MUST NOT introduce new hard-coded colors.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 — upgraded widget remains a function component; uses `React.FC`/hooks; no React 18-only APIs introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Renderer lives in `@spaarke/ui-components`; widget lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets`. The widget imports `RichFilePreview` via the shared-lib package boundary (NOT via a relative cross-package path). Confirm the barrel re-export (task 013 Step 6) is in place before depending on it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">No new PaneEventBus channels; no new event types added by this task (task 016 owns the R5 additive event types). This widget is a CONSUMER of the existing `workspace.widget_load` dispatch — no new event emission required at the widget level.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No token snapshots. The widget itself does NOT call BFF in v1 (text-only path inherits R4 behavior); when future dispatch sites supply a `fetchPreviewUrl` closure, that closure (owned by the dispatch site, NOT the widget) is responsible for fresh-token retrieval per ADR-028.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">No PCF control change in this task. R5 has NO PCF controls per project CLAUDE.md §4.3.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + ADR-029">BFF publish-size — this task is frontend-only (zero BFF code change). Confirm publish-size delta = 0 MB in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7">Test obligation — this task modifies a `@spaarke/ai-widgets` workspace widget. Update existing `DocumentViewerWidget.test.tsx` to reflect the new composition (renderer mounting). Add coverage for: (a) widget mounts `&lt;RichFilePreview /&gt;`; (b) back-compat — R4-style text-only payload still mounts without crashing and renders graceful empty/error state; (c) typed-payload narrowing — invalid `widgetData` does not crash. Existing R4 test cases preserved or explicitly migrated with rationale.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 task scope">Task 018 (`FilePreviewContextWidget`) is a SIBLING consumer of the same extracted renderer for the Context pane (non-modal). This task is the Workspace consumer. Do NOT modify `FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx` or `RichFilePreview.tsx` in this task. Scope is ONLY `DocumentViewerWidget.tsx` (+ co-located tests).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (no scope-creep on payload schema)">Do NOT introduce new BFF endpoints, new Dataverse fields, or new chat-tool dispatch shapes to source preview URLs in this task. Sourcing of `previewUrl` / `fetchPreviewUrl` from dispatch sites is the responsibility of those dispatch sites (task 020 chat-pane orchestration; task 021 per-file affordance; future R6 SharePoint Embedded integration). This task ONLY extends the widget's payload TYPE additively + wires the renderer.</constraint>
  </constraints>

