    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Workspace widget composes shared renderer" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx (post-upgrade)">
        The upgraded widget is a thin `WorkspaceWidgetProps&lt;DocumentViewerWidgetData&gt;`
        consumer: it (a) defensively narrows `data` via the existing
        `isDocumentViewerData` type guard (extended to cover the new optional fields),
        (b) maps the typed payload onto `IRichFilePreviewProps` (documentName,
        documentId, documentType, createdBy, createdAt, fileSize, fetchPreviewUrl,
        and minimal action callbacks), (c) mounts `&lt;RichFilePreview /&gt;` inside a
        light wrapper `&lt;div&gt;` that respects the widget's
        `className`/`data-widget-type`/`data-testid` envelope, and (d) returns the
        graceful empty/error state when narrowing fails. The R4 monospace-preview JSX
        + `previewContainer` + `previewText` + `MAX_INLINE_PREVIEW_CHARS` logic is
        REMOVED — the renderer owns preview rendering now.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Graceful fallback for text-only payloads" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx (post-upgrade)">
        When `data` has no preview URL source (no `previewUrl`, no `fetchPreviewUrl`,
        no `documentId` resolvable to a URL), the widget MUST pass
        `fetchPreviewUrl={async () =&gt; null}` to the renderer. The renderer's
        existing error/retry path (per task 013) handles this case with the
        documented empty-state UX. This preserves R4 dispatch sites that only provide
        in-memory text payloads — they show the renderer's "no preview available"
        state instead of crashing. (R5 dispatch sites in tasks 020 + 021 will pass a
        real `fetchPreviewUrl` closure when SPE preview integration lands; that is
        OUT OF SCOPE for this task.)
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Additive optional fields on typed payload" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx (DocumentViewerWidgetData)">
        Extend `DocumentViewerWidgetData` ADDITIVELY:
        ```ts
        export interface DocumentViewerWidgetData {
          // R4 fields (back-compat, unchanged)
          filename: string;
          contentType: string;
          sizeBytes?: number;
          textContent: string;
          // R5 additions (all optional)
          documentId?: string;
          documentType?: string;
          createdBy?: string | null;
          createdAt?: string | null;
          previewUrl?: string | null;
          fetchPreviewUrl?: () =&gt; Promise&lt;string | null&gt;;
        }
        ```
        Existing R4 dispatch sites compile unchanged; new R5 dispatch sites populate
        the optional fields to power the renderer.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Defensive payload narrowing at the widget boundary" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx (isDocumentViewerData)">
        Keep the existing `isDocumentViewerData` type guard but relax it to accept
        the R4 minimum fields (filename, contentType, textContent) as required. New
        optional fields are NOT required by the guard. When narrowing fails, render
        the renderer's empty state via a `fetchPreviewUrl` that resolves to null and
        a synthesized `documentName = 'Unknown file'`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Existing test pattern preservation" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/__tests__/DocumentViewerWidget.test.tsx">
        The existing test file uses Vitest + testing-library. Preserve the existing
        R4 test cases that exercise payload narrowing + empty/loading/error rendering.
        Update assertions where the R4 stub's monospace preview `&lt;pre&gt;` is
        replaced by the renderer subtree. Add new cases: (a) widget mounts
        `&lt;RichFilePreview /&gt;` (assert via `data-testid` from the renderer); (b)
        text-only payload renders renderer empty state without crashing; (c) typed
        payload with `previewUrl` passes a `fetchPreviewUrl` closure that resolves
        to the URL.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R4 task 042 (W-4) shipped `DocumentViewerWidget` as a SHIM Workspace widget —
      explicitly noted in the file header as a "demo scope" placeholder rendering
      file metadata + a monospace text preview of already-extracted content. The R4
      acceptance for that shim was deliberately narrow: validate the
      Assistant → Workspace `widget_load` dispatch pipeline end-to-end. Broader viewer
      fidelity (PDF.js page render, image preview, RecordViewer integration) was
      called out OUT OF SCOPE in the file header itself, with the implicit
      expectation that a later phase would upgrade the widget to the canonical
      preview UX.

      R5 task 013 extracted the canonical preview renderer (`RichFilePreview`) from
      `RichFilePreviewDialog` into `@spaarke/ui-components` so non-modal consumers
      (Workspace widget — this task; Context-pane widget — task 018) can mount the
      same renderer without the modal `Dialog` envelope. With task 013 complete, the
      shim's reason-for-existence is gone — this task replaces the shim with
      renderer consumption.

      Why this is a separate ticket (not bundled into task 013): per the R5 reuse
      mandate (CLAUDE.md §3.1) and the task-013 POML acceptance criteria, task 013
      explicitly EXCLUDES touching `DocumentViewerWidget.tsx` or
      `FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx` — separating extraction from consumption keeps
      scope tight, makes the diff reviewable, and lets the two consumers (this task
      + task 018) parallelize in P2-G5 / P2-G4 respectively without conflicting
      edits.

      Why we preserve back-compat for R4-style text-only payloads: the R4 dispatch
      site (`useChatFileAttachment` → ConversationPane → `workspace.widget_load`)
      currently produces text-only payloads with no SPE `driveId`/`itemId` or
      preview URL. Phase 2's chat-pane orchestration (task 020) and per-file
      affordance (task 021) will populate optional preview URL fields when they
      land. Keeping the widget back-compat means R4 dispatch sites continue to
      work without modification, the renderer gracefully degrades to its
      empty/error state when no URL source is provided, and R5 dispatch sites
      progressively light up rich preview as they wire it.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="013" status="not-started">
        D2-08 (first half) — extracts `RichFilePreview` renderer from
        `RichFilePreviewDialog` into `@spaarke/ui-components`. This task consumes
        the extracted renderer; task 013 MUST be ✅ before task 022 starts.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>R4 task 042 (W-4) — original `DocumentViewerWidget` SHIM + Workspace
        widget registration. This task upgrades the shim while preserving the
        registration.</item>
      <item>Task 018 (D2-09) `FilePreviewContextWidget` — SIBLING consumer of the
        extracted renderer for the Context-pane (non-modal) destination.
        Parallel-safe in P2-G4. Out of scope for this task; same extracted-renderer
        consumption pattern.</item>
      <item>Task 020 (D2-11) chat-pane orchestration UX — future R5 dispatch site
        that will populate the new optional `previewUrl`/`fetchPreviewUrl` fields
        on `DocumentViewerWidgetData` to drive the renderer's full rich preview.
        Out of scope for this task; explicitly NOT a dependency.</item>
      <item>Task 021 (D2-12) per-file "Summarize this only" affordance — additional
        future R5 dispatch site that may also supply a preview URL source. Out of
        scope for this task; explicitly NOT a dependency.</item>
      <item>R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate — explicit prohibition on a "parallel
        file-preview component to `RichFilePreviewDialog`". This task is the
        Workspace consumption half of that mandate (task 013 is the extraction
        half; task 018 is the Context-pane consumption half).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

