        mapping function `mapPayloadToRendererProps(data: DocumentViewerWidgetData):
        IRichFilePreviewProps`, default `fetchPreviewUrl` closure that resolves to
        null when no URL source is provided, default no-op action callbacks for
        actions the widget does not currently surface (open file, open record,
        email, copy link — wire to a no-op + telemetry warning until R5 dispatch
        sites land in tasks 020 / 021).
      - Decision on `disabledActions`: per task 013, `RichFilePreview` accepts
        an optional `disabledActions` override. For the Workspace destination,
        hide the same default set the dialog hides (preview, aiSummary,
        toggleWorkspace, rename) PLUS hide findSimilar when no `onFindSimilar`
        callback is supplied. Document this default in the widget file's
        header comment.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Replace R4 Stub Body with RichFilePreview Consumption">
      Edit
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx`:
      - Update the file header comment to reflect the upgrade (cite task 022 + this
        plan, supersede the R4 demo-scope note, keep ADR compliance summary).
      - Extend `DocumentViewerWidgetData` with the additive optional fields per
        the Step 3 pattern.
      - Relax `isDocumentViewerData` to validate ONLY the R4 minimum required
        fields; new optional fields pass through unchecked at the guard level.
      - Replace the JSX body. Outer wrapper `&lt;div&gt;` keeps
        `className`/`data-widget-type`/`data-testid`. Inside, mount
        `&lt;RichFilePreview {...mappedProps} /&gt;` imported from
        `@spaarke/ui-components`. Map payload → renderer props per Step 3.
      - Remove the R4 shim styles (`previewContainer`, `previewText`, `emptyState`,
        `truncationNotice`, `metadataRow`, `headerIcon`, `headerTitle`,
        `headerSubtitle`, `card`). Keep only `root` (wrapper). Trim `useStyles` to
        match.
      - Remove `MAX_INLINE_PREVIEW_CHARS` + `formatFileSize` + `isPdf` (no longer
        needed; the renderer owns these concerns).
      - Default action callbacks: pass a small set of no-op + telemetry-warning
        callbacks for `onOpenFile`, `onOpenRecord`, `onEmailDocument`,
        `onCopyLink`. Surface a `console.warn` in dev builds so future R5 dispatch
        sites (tasks 020/021) know to supply real callbacks. Do NOT throw.
      - Keep `displayName` / default export shape unchanged so the registration
        in `register-document-viewer-widget.ts` continues to resolve.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify Workspace Tab Dispatch is Unchanged">
      Do NOT modify `register-document-viewer-widget.ts`. Confirm:
      - `DOCUMENT_VIEWER_WIDGET_TYPE = 'document-viewer'` literal unchanged.
      - `registerWorkspaceWidget` call signature unchanged: displayName 'Document
        Viewer', category 'document', icon 'DocumentRegular',
        `allowMultiple: true`, `defaultOrder: 150`.
