  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`DocumentViewerWidget.tsx` is upgraded: the R4 monospace-text-preview JSX subtree (`Card` / `CardHeader` / `previewContainer` / `&lt;pre&gt;` / `MAX_INLINE_PREVIEW_CHARS` truncation logic) is REMOVED, replaced by a thin wrapper that mounts `&lt;RichFilePreview /&gt;` imported from `@spaarke/ui-components`. Diff evidence in task notes confirms the renderer is CONSUMED (not rebuilt).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Widget registration UNCHANGED: `register-document-viewer-widget.ts` is NOT modified by this task. `DOCUMENT_VIEWER_WIDGET_TYPE = 'document-viewer'`, displayName, category, icon, `allowMultiple: true`, `defaultOrder: 150` all preserved. The dynamic import resolves to the upgraded module.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`DocumentViewerWidgetData` shape is back-compat: existing R4 required fields (`filename`, `contentType`, `textContent`) + optional `sizeBytes?` are unchanged; new R5 fields (`documentId?`, `documentType?`, `createdBy?`, `createdAt?`, `previewUrl?`, `fetchPreviewUrl?`) are ADDITIVE + OPTIONAL.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Existing R4 dispatch sites (e.g. ConversationPane via `useChatFileAttachment` → `workspace.widget_load`) compile with NO change to dispatch payload. `tsc --noEmit` clean across `@spaarke/ai-widgets` and downstream consumer packages. Back-compat verification matrix recorded in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Graceful degrade verified: a back-compat text-only payload (no `previewUrl`, no `fetchPreviewUrl`) mounts `RichFilePreview` with a `fetchPreviewUrl` closure that resolves to `null`; the renderer's existing empty/error state renders without crash. The widget DOES NOT regress to the R4 monospace `&lt;pre&gt;` element.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">R5 dispatch path verified: a synthetic payload with `previewUrl: '...'` causes the renderer to receive a `fetchPreviewUrl` closure that resolves to that URL (asserted via test mock or passed-prop inspection).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Defensive narrowing verified: invalid `widgetData` (failing `isDocumentViewerData`) does not crash; renderer mounts with `documentName = 'Unknown file'` and a null-resolving `fetchPreviewUrl`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark-mode parity verified — upgraded widget renders correctly in light + dark themes; no hard-coded color literals introduced; all colors flow through Fluent v9 semantic tokens. Evidence captured in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tests pass: existing R4 test cases preserved or explicitly migrated with rationale; new cases cover renderer consumption + back-compat text-only payload + R5 payload + defensive narrowing. `npm test` clean.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scope discipline: `RichFilePreview.tsx` is NOT modified by this task. `FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx` is NOT modified or created by this task. `register-document-viewer-widget.ts` is NOT modified by this task. (Negative criteria — confirms task boundaries.)</criterion>
